gurmukhi: duhW kMDwrW muih juVy; s`t peI jmDwx k`au ]
transliteration: Duhaan Kandhaaraan Muh(i) Jude Satt Paijamdhaan Kau||
translation: The trumpet, enveloped by the hide of the male buffalo, the vehicle of Yama, was beaten and both the armies faced each other.

gurmukhi: qd iKMg nsMuB ncwieAw; fwl aupir brgsqwx k`au ]
transliteration: Tad Khing Nasounbh Nachaaiaa Daal Oupar(i) Baragadtaan Kau||
translation: Then Nisumbh caused the horse to dance, putting on his back the saddle-armour.

gurmukhi: PVI iblMd mMgwieaus; Purmwies kir mulqwn k`au ]
transliteration: Phadibiland Magadeous Phurmaaes Kar(i) Multaan Kau||
translation: She held the big bow, which was caused to be brought on order form Musltan.

gurmukhi: gu`sy AweI swmHxy; rx AMdir G`qx Gwx k`au ]
transliteration: Gousse Aaisahmane Ran Andar(i) Ghattan Ghaan Kau||
translation: In her fury, she came in front in order to fill the battlefield with the mud of blood and fat.

gurmukhi: AgY qyg vgweI durgswh; b`F sMuBn bhI plwx k`au ]
transliteration: Agad Teg Vagadidurgsaah Badh Sounbhuan Bahipalaan Kau||
translation: Durga struck the sword in front of her, cutting the demon-king, penetrated through the horse-saddle.

gurmukhi: rVkI jwie kY Drq k`au; b`F pwKr b`F ikkwx k`au ]
transliteration: Radkijaae Kai Dharat Kau Baddh Paakhar Baddh Kikaan Kau||
translation: Then it penetrated further and struck the earth after cutting the saddle-armour and the horse.

gurmukhi: bIr plwxo if`igAw; kir isjdw sMuB sujwx k`au ]
transliteration: Beer Palaano Diggiaa Kar(i) Sijdaa Sounbh Sujaan Kau||
translation: The great hero (Nisumbh) fell down from the horse-saddle, offering salutation to the wise Sumbh.
Hail, hail, to the winsome chieftain (Khan).
Hail, hail, ever to thy strength.
Praises are offered for the chewing of betel.

gurmukhi: durgw AqY dwnvI; gh sMGir k`Qy ]
translation: Durga and demons sounded their trumpets, in the remarkable war.
